                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-2015-offence-1 t18420613-name-1494"></join>John Waude</persName>, his master</rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1495" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1495" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1495" type="surname" value="WAUDE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1495" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WAUDE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coach-builder, living in Kent-road. The pri<lb></lb>soner was in my service some years as coach-maker. About the 31st of May, I missed a quantity of leather—I saw this leather in Mr. Judkins' shop—It is the cutting of my skins—to the best of my belief it is mine—on Monday, the 13th of May, I had information from one of my men, and spoke to the prisoner about the leather—he said it was the first time he had committed any offence, and hoped I would forgive him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> These are cuttings? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, to make elbows, and other parts of seats—they are worth 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I merely institute this, for the sake of example to my men—I always had the highest opinion of the prisoner—he had an opportunity of taking more valuable property</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1496" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1496" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1496" type="surname" value="HOLMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1496" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HOLMES</persName>
                  </hi> I am in the service of Mr. Judkins. I bought this leather of the prisoner at 1s. a 1b.—there is about 31b.—it is the Full value.</p>
